    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-25T21:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-25T21:40:00-05:00" n="800"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00 Revolutions/14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-25T22:00:00-04:40"
                            >February 25, 1930—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Your February 25, 3 p.m. Both the Government and the Opposition have at all
                    times shown every disposition to respect American lives and property.
                    Nevertheless there has been serious danger of unorganized street fighting and
                    rioting and if this occurs there will be no time for an American warship to come
                    even from a short distance.</p>
                <p>Cabot has lately returned with proposals of the leaders of the revolution and
                    there seem to be good prospects of an agreement being reached.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
